{"lemma":"سَمَكِ","slug":"سَمَكِ","root":"س.م.ك","root_slug":"س-م-ك","root_link":"/words/roots/س-م-ك","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"سَمَكِ","root":"سمك","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n20755","n20756","n20757"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%8E%D9%83%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fish","tags":["collective"],"examples":[{"text":"السَّرْدِينُ عِبَارَةٌ عَنْ سَمَكٍ مُدْهِنٍ صَغِيرٍ يُمْكِنُ أَكْلُهُ دُونَ مَضْغ.","english":"Sardines are small, oily fish that can be eaten whole."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to thicken"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"thickness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"roof, ceiling"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root س م ك (s m k), meaning “to be elevated or lofty”, “to be supported or held up”, “to sustain”; hence the meaning of “a source of sustenance”, “a mainstay or staple-food”. Cognate with Hebrew סָמַך (samak, “to lean, lay, rest, support”) attested in the Bible with the similar semantic sense “to sustain” or “to nourish”.\n\nFrom the root س م ك (s m k) in the sense of \"to nourish\", \"to make well-fed\", \"to fatten up livestock\".\n\nFrom the root س م ك (s m k), in the sense of \"to be elevated or lofty\", \"to be supported or held up\"."},"ipa":["/sa.mak/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n20755","headword_ar":"سَمَكَ","root":"smk","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", [aor."},{"kind":"text","text":",] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sumuwkN","text_ar":"سُمُوكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a thing)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rose,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became high"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"elevated"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lofty."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) ―         -b2-  And, aor. and inf. n. as above,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He ascended."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ausomuko fiY Alr~ayomi","text_ar":"اُسْمُكْ فِى الرَّيْمِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ascend thou the stairs."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA. [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rayomN","text_ar":"رَيْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".])       -A2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samakahu","text_ar":"سَمَكَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) aor. as above, (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samokN","text_ar":"سَمْكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He raised, elevated, upraised,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uplifted, it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) So in the phrase,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samaka A@ll~`hu Als~amaA='a","text_ar":"سَمَكَ ا@للّٰهُ السَّمَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God raised the heaven"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n20756","headword_ar":"سَمْكٌ","root":"smk","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"roof"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a house, or chamber: (S, Mgh, * K: *) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"interior uppermost part"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ceiling"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of a house, or chamber; the exterior uppermost part thereof being called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SahowapN","text_ar":"صَهْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Ham p. 725:) or [the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"height"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the top to the bottom"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a house or chamber. (K.) [And hence, The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"canopy"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the heaven or sky: or] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"measure of the height"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the heaven"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the earth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thickness"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upwards."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd in lxxix. 28.) And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stature,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"height in a standing posture,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or anything: (K:) thus expl. by Lth: one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biEiyrN Tawiylu Als~amoki","text_ar":"بِعِيرٌ طَوِيلُ السَّمْكِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A camel tall of stature"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) [In the present day, it signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extent"},{"kind":"text","text":"of anything"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from top to bottom;"},{"kind":"text","text":"its"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"height, depth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thickness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and is vulgarly pronounced"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sumok","text_ar":"سُمْك"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["K"]},{"entry_id":"n20757","headword_ar":"سَمَكٌ","root":"smk","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fish;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuwtN","text_ar":"حُوتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of aquatic creatures:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a coll. gen. n.:] n. un. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": pl. of the former"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"simaAkN","text_ar":"سِمَاكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sumuwkN","text_ar":"سُمُوكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$awaY","text_ar":"شَوَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY AlHariyqi samakatahu","text_ar":"فِى الحَرِيقِ سَمَكَتَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He broiled his fish in the fire of a burning house"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is a post-classical prov. of the people of Baghdád, relating to the concealing, disguising, or cloaking, of a fault, for the purpose of seizing an opportunity; orginating from the fact that the thief used, when he saw the fire of a burning house in a place, to go thither for the purpose of theft; and if it were in his power, he did what he desired; and if he were lighted on, he said, I came to broil a fish. (Mtr, in Har pp. 481-2.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~amakapu","text_ar":"السَّمَكَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[is a name of (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The constellation Pisces;"},{"kind":"text","text":"also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~amakataAni","text_ar":"السَّمَكَتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":";]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain sign of the Zodiac;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) thought by ISd to be so called because it is a watery sign; and also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHuwtu","text_ar":"الحُوتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}